OL,6,FThe PFA survey also revealed that
OL,7,Finjury remained the issue that most
OL,8,Faffected player well-being, with 64%
OL,9,Fof players highlighting this as a
OL,10,Fconcern.
OL,12,FPressure to perform also remained a
OL,13,Fwidespread issue, with 46% of players
OL,14,Frevealing it played on their minds.
OL,16,FMeanwhile, more than 41% of players
OL,17,Fworried about relationships and 32%
OL,18,Fabout their families, while 32%
OL,19,Freported experiencing low mood,
OL,20,Firritability, or anger.
